public abstract class BaseFeatureClass
extends BaseMapDataset
implements FeatureClass

A partial implementation of FeatureClass. To implement your own FeatureClass, you have to implement the getData method, since DataIDs are normally implementation-specific.

Note: This is a partial implementation of getData() which should be referenced by the subclasses.

The search method provided invokes searchEnvelope, which must be implemented by the subclass and will return all features for a given envelope. The search method then applies the given QueryFilter to the result.

You can choose to implement your own search method too.

A subclass will normally implement this method if it is considered desirable to use the search method implemented in this class.

search
